div.div:
$NOTES
In order to sort beads, the robot must be trained on what colors are present in the bin.
The number of bead colors MUST exactly match BEAD_COLOR_COUNT in Constants.hpp. If they don't match, you will likely get unexpected results.
The number of possible clusters is equal to BEAD_COLOR_COUNT+2. This is because there are two special clusters
-- if the bead picker is empty, the sensor will read a color similar to the color of your servo box plastic.
-- if the bead picker is jammed, the sensor will read a color similar to the color of your picker
For this reason, we seed the training with 5 empty reads and 5 simulated "jammed" reads before we start picking up real beads.
Training is complete once the k-means algorithm stabilizes with at least 5 reads of each bead color.
